LINE L.A is a new Los Angeles hotel collaboration with re-imagined public spaces and guest rooms designed by Sean Knibb. The hotel is the first to draw inspiration from the distinct Korean culture of its surrounding neighborhood and includes two restaurants by Koreatown's own Roy Choi (celebrated chef behind Kogi, Chego and A-Frame), nightlife by the Houston brothers (the duo responsible for prominent LA lounges such as La Descarga and Harvard &amp; Stone), and noted art and design shop Poketo.<br>
<br>
A partnership between Ron Burkle and Andrew Zobler, the Sydell Group is the creator and manager of unique hotels rooted in their location and architecture. Sydell's core expertise is an ability to collaborate with original talent within the world of design, food &amp; beverage, and retail, and bring them together in the creation of compelling new hotels that engage the communities around them. Sydell Group's diverse portfolio of award-winning properties include The NoMad, New York; The <br>
<br>
Mini Bar Attendant <br>
<br>
Job overview: <br>
Stock and replenish in-room private or mini-bar. <br>
<br>
ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:<br>
<br>
1.	Stock and replenish private bar items, and compute and relay guest charges accurately to Front Office. (30%)<br>
2.	Keep an accurate par if food items such as beverages and snacks, as well as non-food items like menu cards, napkins, straws, etc. on cart and in storage areas.  (20%)<br>
3.	Clean and maintain in-room private/mini-bars; report damage, or malfunctioning units.  (15%)<br>
4.	Check quality and expiration of all items; discard and replace according to established procedures. (15%)<br>
5.	Comply The Line Work Rules and Standards of Conduct as set forth in the Guide Line. (10%)<br>
6.	Work harmoniously and professionally with co-workers and supervisors.  (10%)<br>
<br>
<br>
KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS:<br>
 <br>
Education: 	High school education or equivalent experience.<br>
<br>
Experience:	Minimum 6 months food service or related work.	<br>
<br>
Skills and Abilities:	Ability to count and record accurately.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
